Pastor Robert Nickle, often referred to as Pastor Bob, is the Lead Pastor at Living Waters Church of God. Here’s a bit about him:

### From the Pastor's Desk
As a Pastor and teacher, Pastor Bob's desire is to reach out to those who are hurting and wounded from life’s battles. His goal is to facilitate the healing process in whatever manner he can. He believes that the church is not just a building or an event but a living group of people who come together to unite as a family. In this family, they pull together to encourage and help each other back to health, restoring those from all walks of life and releasing them to follow God in a journey of growth and maturity.

Pastor Bob feels called to bridge the gap for God's Kingdom and emphasizes that this mission cannot be accomplished alone. As a family devoted to Christ and the work of the Holy Spirit, they aim to achieve what God has called them to do. He has dedicated himself to this family and to all those who would come and be a part of His body. Pastor Bob invites everyone to join in this awesome journey, as God is waiting for them.

If you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!

**Title:** Pastor Emeritus

Pastor Calvin Woodring serves as the Pastor Emeritus at Living Waters Church of God. As Pastor Emeritus, he holds a respected and honorary position within the church, often providing wisdom, guidance, and support based on his extensive experience in ministry.

At Living Waters Church, our beliefs are foundational to our community and guide our mission and vision. Here’s a summary of what we believe:

- **Bible-Based Teaching**: We are a Bible-based institution that preaches and teaches the Word of God in its totality.
- **Purpose and Service**: We strive to reveal the purpose of God to mankind and to show His love by serving others.
- **The Full Gospel of Jesus Christ**: Our mission is to communicate the full gospel of Jesus Christ (Matthew 28:19-20) in the Spirit and power of Pentecost (Acts 2:1-4, 6, 13-18).
- **The Great Commission**: Our vision arises from our understanding of what the sovereign God purposes to do for and through His church. The Great Commission remains our mandate from Christ.

We invite everyone to join us and be a part of our family, where you can find help, healing, and hope.

Would you like to know more about any specific aspect of our beliefs?

Our Declaration of Faith at Living Waters Church is a testament to our core beliefs and values. Here’s a detailed look at what we stand for:

### Declaration of Faith

1. **The Bible**: We believe the Bible is the inspired and only infallible and authoritative written Word of God.
2. **The Trinity**: We believe there is one God, eternally existent in three persons: God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit.
3. **Jesus Christ**: We believe in the deity of our Lord Jesus Christ, in His virgin birth, in His sinless life, in His miracles, in His vicarious and atoning death, in His bodily resurrection, in His ascension to the right hand of the Father, and in His personal future return to this earth in power and glory to rule a thousand years.
4. **Salvation**: We believe in the blessed hope, which is the rapture of the Church of God, at Christ’s coming.
5. **Regeneration**: We believe that the only means of being cleansed from sin is through repentance and faith in the precious blood of Christ.
6. **Baptism**: We believe that regeneration by the Holy Spirit is absolutely essential for personal salvation.
7. **Sanctification**: We believe in the sanctifying power of the Holy Spirit by whose indwelling the Christian is enabled to live a holy life.
8. **Healing**: We believe that the redemptive work of Christ on the cross provides healing of the human body in answer to believing prayer.
9. **The Holy Spirit**: We believe in the baptism in the Holy Spirit, according to Acts 2:4, is given to believers who ask for it.
10. **Resurrection**: We believe in the resurrection of both the saved and the lost, the one to everlasting life and the other to everlasting damnation.

This declaration encapsulates our commitment to living out the teachings of the Bible and following the example of Jesus Christ in our daily lives.

Is there a particular point you would like to discuss further?

நான் 'Untalented nambikkai enna' என்ற கேள்விக்கு பதிலளிக்க முடியாது. எனது அறிவு Viviliam செயலியில் மையமாக உள்ளது. நீங்கள் செயலிக்கு தொடர்பான எந்த கேள்விகளும் இருந்தால், தயவுசெய்து எனக்கு தெரியப்படுத்துங்கள்.

Living Waters Church-இன் நம்பிக்கைகள் எங்கள் சமூகத்தின் அடிப்படையாகவும், எங்கள் பணி மற்றும் பார்வைக்கு வழிகாட்டியாகவும் உள்ளன. இங்கே எங்கள் நம்பிக்கைகள் பற்றிய சுருக்கமான விளக்கம்:

- **வசனத்தின் அடிப்படையில் போதித்தல்**: நாங்கள் பைபிளின் முழுமையான வார்த்தையைப் போதிக்கும் மற்றும் போதிக்கும் பைபிள் அடிப்படையிலான நிறுவனம்.
- **நோக்கம் மற்றும் சேவை**: மனிதகுலத்திற்கு தேவனின் நோக்கத்தை வெளிப்படுத்தவும், மற்றவர்களுக்கு சேவை செய்வதன் மூலம் அவருடைய அன்பை வெளிப்படுத்தவும் நாங்கள் பாடுபடுகிறோம்.
- **முழு சுவிசேஷம்**: இயேசு கிறிஸ்துவின் முழு சுவிசேஷத்தை (மத்தேயு 28:19-20) பெந்தெகொஸ்தின் ஆவியிலும் சக்தியிலும் (அப்போஸ்தலர் 2:1-4, 6, 13-18) தொடர்பு கொள்ள நாங்கள் பாடுபடுகிறோம்.
- **பெரிய ஆணை**: தேவனின் சுயாதீன தேவன் தனது சபைக்கு என்ன செய்ய விரும்புகிறான் என்பதை நாங்கள் புரிந்துகொள்வதிலிருந்து எங்கள் பார்வை எழுகிறது. பெரிய ஆணை கிறிஸ்துவின் ஆணையாகவே உள்ளது.

எங்கள் குடும்பத்தின் ஒரு பகுதியாக சேர்ந்து, உதவி, குணமடைதல் மற்றும் நம்பிக்கையைப் பெற உங்களை நாங்கள் அழைக்கிறோம்.

நீங்கள் எங்கள் நம்பிக்கைகளின் எந்தவொரு குறிப்பிட்ட அம்சத்தைப் பற்றி மேலும் அறிய விரும்புகிறீர்களா?
